      "title": "[Boing Boing] A YouTuber rebuilt a mercury light bulb discovered in 1675",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Mercury_light_bulb-scaled.jpg?fit=2560%2C1920&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 0.75em;padding:5px 10px;background:#f0f4f8;border-left:3px solid #7b9fc4;border-radius:3px;font-size:0.82em;color:#444;line-height:1.8;\">🎨 🌾 🔭 <a href=\"https://zirnhelt.github.io/super-rss-feed/review.html?url=https%3A%2F%2Fboingboing.net%2F2026%2F07%2F23%2Fpost-a-youtuber-rebuilt-the-glowing-light-discovered-by.html\" style=\"color:#7b9fc4;text-decoration:none;\">✏️</a></p>\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/23/post-a-youtuber-rebuilt-the-glowing-light-discovered-by.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"A YouTuber rebuilt a mercury light bulb discovered in 1675\"><img alt=\"mercury light bulb — &quot;Mercury light bulb&quot; by Dmitry G is licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0.\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Mercury_light_bulb-scaled.jpg?fit=2560%2C1920&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"2560\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In 1675, the French astronomer Jean Picard noticed something strange while carrying his mercury barometer through a dark room: the mercury glowed as it sloshed around the bulb. Two centuries before Edison, he had stumbled onto a working light source. The effect became a favorite puzzle for the leading scientists of the day, who called it barometric light. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/23/post-a-youtuber-rebuilt-the-glowing-light-discovered-by.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/23/post-a-youtuber-rebuilt-the-glowing-light-discovered-by.html\">A YouTuber rebuilt a mercury light bulb discovered in 1675</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
