d1ce4dfc9d1a6cd9f59412b1%2Fsci-221-26-3d-printing-rigid-contact-lens-article-photos-shirley-tang-12.jpg\" /><p>Contact lens technology has come a long way. Early lenses were made from glass, and were uncomfortable to wear for an entire day. Today, lenses are made from soft materials such as silicone hydrogel and they are barely noticeable on the eye.</p><p><a href=\"https://newatlas.com/3d-printing/3d-printed-custom-contact-lenses-20-minutes/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/3d-printing/\">3D Printing</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/manufacturing/\">Manufacturing</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/engineering/\">Engineering</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/university-of-waterloo/\" rel=\"tag\">University of Waterloo</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/contact-lens/\" rel=\"tag\">Contact Lenses</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/vision/\" rel=\"tag\">Vision</a></p>",
